WEBVTT

00:04.605 --> 00:07.341
"Faster
Than the Speed of Light"]

00:14.482 --> 00:17.685
The year was 1971.

00:17.685 --> 00:22.356
Hot pants and bell bottoms
were the latest trends.

00:22.356 --> 00:25.293
Simon and Garfunkel's
Bridge Over Troubled Water

00:25.293 --> 00:27.695
was album of the year.

00:27.695 --> 00:31.199
And a controversial new sitcom
called in All in the Family

00:31.199 --> 00:32.800
premiered in prime-time.

00:35.469 --> 00:38.106
Playboy had grown bigger
than ever before...

00:39.840 --> 00:43.444
... thanks to increasing
magazine sales

00:43.444 --> 00:46.247
and over 15 Playboy clubs
around the world.

00:48.015 --> 00:49.717
On top of the clubs,

00:49.717 --> 00:52.920
we'd also started opening
luxury vacation resorts.

00:52.920 --> 00:56.724
Mr. Hefner has spent
no less than $10 million

00:56.724 --> 00:59.427
in building a resort
that makes the Taj Mahal

00:59.427 --> 01:00.594
look like a Quonset hut.

01:03.631 --> 01:05.133
Okay, let's shoot.

01:05.133 --> 01:06.467
Action!

01:06.467 --> 01:07.801
We also expanded into

01:07.801 --> 01:09.603
even more side ventures,

01:09.603 --> 01:12.340
including a TV and film
production company.

01:14.308 --> 01:16.944
We produced an adaptation
of "Macbeth,"

01:16.944 --> 01:18.746
directed by Roman Polanski...

01:21.215 --> 01:22.716
... and the first movie

01:22.716 --> 01:25.719
from the British comedy
troupe, Monty Python.

01:28.489 --> 01:30.424
The Playboy brand
was recognized

01:30.424 --> 01:33.627
all over the world...

01:33.627 --> 01:36.697
and what had started
as just a magazine

01:36.697 --> 01:39.400
was now a multinational
entertainment corporation

01:39.400 --> 01:43.371
worth $200 million.

01:43.371 --> 01:46.340
Nike is a brand, but Reebok
is a shoe company.

01:46.340 --> 01:49.143
Virgin is a brand,
United is an airline.

01:49.143 --> 01:51.512
Playboy was a brand,

01:51.512 --> 01:54.114
and that means
that you can move

01:54.114 --> 01:55.516
from one category
to another,

01:55.516 --> 01:58.486
because you represent
not a single product

01:58.486 --> 02:00.120
but an attitude toward life.

02:01.889 --> 02:03.591
Our success made us
very attractive

02:03.591 --> 02:05.293
to Wall Street investors...

02:07.195 --> 02:10.698
... so that year I decided
to take the company public.

02:12.400 --> 02:14.702
Playboy goes public.

02:14.702 --> 02:17.638
Now you bring in a tremendous
amount of capital,

02:17.638 --> 02:19.907
which you can then reinvest,

02:19.907 --> 02:23.043
and it's a signal
of the kind of normalization

02:23.043 --> 02:25.713
of the pornography business.

02:25.713 --> 02:26.914
I mean, what's
more establishment

02:26.914 --> 02:27.848
than Wall Street?

02:29.750 --> 02:32.820
The influx of cash
was a huge boost,

02:32.820 --> 02:35.323
and it felt good to have
the world acknowledge Playboy

02:35.323 --> 02:38.025
as a legitimate business.

02:38.025 --> 02:41.729
But the magazine was still
facing one major challenge.

02:47.501 --> 02:50.438
Ongoing competition
from Penthouse.

02:57.044 --> 02:58.712
Since 1969,

02:58.712 --> 03:00.814
Penthouse had been
pushing the envelope

03:00.814 --> 03:03.784
with pictures that
made Playboy look tame.

03:08.356 --> 03:12.326
Over the past two years,
they kept getting raunchier,

03:12.326 --> 03:15.596
and their subscription
had grown by 600%,

03:15.596 --> 03:18.532
to 1.3 million per month.

03:22.035 --> 03:25.839
Playboy still had nearly
five times as many readers,

03:25.839 --> 03:27.841
but I knew that if we
were going to continue

03:27.841 --> 03:30.711
to stay ahead
of the competition,

03:30.711 --> 03:32.646
Playboy would have to show

03:32.646 --> 03:36.250
a lot more than
we ever had before.

03:36.250 --> 03:39.987
* Every little movement *

03:39.987 --> 03:44.224
* Every little thing
you do *

03:44.224 --> 03:46.860
* Is it slight of hand *

03:46.860 --> 03:52.132
* That commands my heart
to love you? *

03:52.132 --> 03:56.370
* Every little movement *

03:56.370 --> 03:59.607
* Every little movement **

04:11.819 --> 04:14.355
So what do you think
we should do?

04:14.355 --> 04:16.757
Honestly? Nothing.

04:16.757 --> 04:19.059
Do you honestly want to
publish pictures like that?

04:19.059 --> 04:21.228
No, I want to publish
better pictures.

04:21.228 --> 04:22.296
And I know we can.

04:22.296 --> 04:24.332
Respectfully,
we already do.

04:24.332 --> 04:26.367
Agreed.

04:28.336 --> 04:30.404
This has to do
with Playboy's brand.

04:30.404 --> 04:31.972
What do you want that
to be?

04:31.972 --> 04:33.507
The best!

04:33.507 --> 04:35.142
We have the best
photographers in the world

04:35.142 --> 04:36.777
begging to work with us.

04:36.777 --> 04:39.580
We didn't get where we are
by being complacent.

04:39.580 --> 04:42.049
There is so much more we can
explore, more we can do,

04:42.049 --> 04:44.985
without losing sight
of what Playboy is about.

04:47.321 --> 04:51.692
Playboy had shown a glimpse of
pubic hair earlier in the year,

04:51.692 --> 04:56.497
but until now, I'd been
hesitant to do it again.

04:56.497 --> 04:57.931
Hef always stayed away

04:57.931 --> 05:00.033
from showing
full frontal nudity,

05:00.033 --> 05:06.774
but Playboy was actually losing
subscribers over to Penthouse.

05:06.774 --> 05:09.443
So Hef was pushed
in the direction

05:09.443 --> 05:11.512
of upping the game.

05:11.512 --> 05:14.782
I knew we needed to publish
a full-frontal centerfold,

05:14.782 --> 05:17.751
but I wanted to do it
the Playboy way,

05:17.751 --> 05:20.821
with polish and sophistication.

05:20.821 --> 05:25.493
To pull it off, we'd need
to find the perfect model.

05:25.493 --> 05:29.096
Luckily, Victor Lownes knew
just the girl for the job.

05:29.096 --> 05:31.832
"Cody Cody"]

05:44.044 --> 05:49.683
She was a bunny working
at the London Playboy Club...

05:49.683 --> 05:52.319
named Marilyn Cole.

05:52.319 --> 05:55.456
Marilyn had
a fantastic figure.

05:56.824 --> 05:59.893
I sent snapshots
of her to Chicago

05:59.893 --> 06:03.431
and said they ought to test
this girl for Playmate material.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.736
I was quite surprised

06:08.736 --> 06:11.071
when Victor suggested
I should be a Playmate.

06:16.276 --> 06:19.580
Not having been a model,

06:19.580 --> 06:22.516
he was the one who
sort of discovered me,

06:22.516 --> 06:25.385
and then I was sent
to Chicago.

06:33.961 --> 06:35.929
Lownes was right.

06:35.929 --> 06:38.966
Marilyn was the perfect
centerfold.

06:43.871 --> 06:45.338
But her photo represented

06:45.338 --> 06:47.508
a whole new direction
forPlayboy.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.050
It's Miss January.

06:58.686 --> 07:01.121
I'm getting a lot
of push-back from spec.

07:01.121 --> 07:02.289
And art.

07:02.289 --> 07:04.191
Would you print it?

07:04.191 --> 07:05.726
Are you kidding me, Hef?

07:05.726 --> 07:08.295
We both know you've
already made up your mind.

07:08.295 --> 07:10.631
Yeah, maybe.

07:11.865 --> 07:16.504
"It's All a Roundabout"]

07:16.504 --> 07:20.240
In January of 1972,

07:20.240 --> 07:24.044
Marilyn Cole became our first
ever full frontal centerfold.

07:26.547 --> 07:29.116
The issue was our
biggest seller to date.

07:30.818 --> 07:34.454
I became the first
full-frontal nude.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.490
What a legacy, but anyway...

07:36.490 --> 07:39.326
I've often been asked,
how did it feel?

07:39.326 --> 07:44.097
And I always think, "Well,
the point that you disrobe,

07:44.097 --> 07:46.667
you become someone else."

07:48.368 --> 07:49.903
That's the only way
you do it.

07:53.006 --> 07:56.409
It did cause a sensation,
certainly here in Britain,

07:56.409 --> 07:58.078
because, "A,"
I was English,

07:58.078 --> 08:00.480
and, "B," it was tabloid press
at that time.

08:02.215 --> 08:05.452
When she showed them to her
mother, her mother said,

08:05.452 --> 08:07.120
"Your hair looks
very nice, dear."

08:07.120 --> 08:09.089
That was her mother's
only comment.

08:13.160 --> 08:17.230
From that point on,
there was no turning back.

08:19.700 --> 08:21.902
By the end of 1972,

08:21.902 --> 08:24.237
our circulation
exceeded seven million,

08:24.237 --> 08:29.276
the highest it had ever been,
so we had a lot to celebrate.

08:47.027 --> 08:50.363
Hey, Kretch?
This is my boyfriend, Ron.

08:50.363 --> 08:51.498
Hi.

08:51.498 --> 08:52.933
In those days,

08:52.933 --> 08:54.635
no one seemed happier
than my longtime friend

08:54.635 --> 08:57.504
and personal assistant,
Bobbie Arnstein.

08:57.504 --> 09:01.742
She had recently started dating
a man named Ron Scharf.

09:01.742 --> 09:03.476
I've seen your issue.
My favorite.

09:03.476 --> 09:05.012
Hey, this is Hef.

09:06.213 --> 09:07.581
Hugh Hefner, hi.

09:07.581 --> 09:08.682
Ron.

09:08.682 --> 09:09.883
Nice to meet you,
finally.

09:09.883 --> 09:11.151
You, too, I've heard
a lot about you.

09:11.151 --> 09:13.386
Okay, we're gonna
take a tour.

09:13.386 --> 09:15.288
Enjoy dinner!

09:15.288 --> 09:16.757
Come on.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.191
So this
is the great room...

09:24.564 --> 09:28.068
I wasn't crazy
about her new boyfriend,

09:28.068 --> 09:30.570
but I did like to see
Bobbie happy.

09:38.245 --> 09:42.082
For over a decade,
Bobbie had been my assistant,

09:42.082 --> 09:45.619
but she'd also become
one of my closest friends.

09:49.757 --> 09:51.992
She lived full-time
at the mansion,

09:51.992 --> 09:54.662
so she was always around
when I needed her.

09:54.662 --> 09:57.397
Bobbie became absolutely
indispensable to me.

09:57.397 --> 09:59.900
Not only because of
the role that she played,

09:59.900 --> 10:03.103
but also because of her own
particular abilities.

10:05.773 --> 10:09.576
She had a remarkable
sensitivity and sense of humor.

10:09.576 --> 10:12.345
And was uncommonly bright.

10:13.981 --> 10:16.817
Bobbie was also part
of my social life.

10:19.687 --> 10:21.621
Okay, don't forget,
on Thursday

10:21.621 --> 10:23.356
you've got a meeting
at the mayor's office.

10:23.356 --> 10:25.793
And then Friday,
board meeting at 2:00 p.m.,

10:25.793 --> 10:27.060
so you gotta
look sharp for that.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.462
I left your gray suit out.
It's been pressed.

10:29.462 --> 10:32.165
Any questions,
talk to Dick.

10:32.165 --> 10:35.769
I don't know how I'm going to
survive without you, Bobbie.

10:35.769 --> 10:37.404
You'll be fine.

10:37.404 --> 10:38.706
All right.

10:38.706 --> 10:39.840
Have a safe trip.

10:43.711 --> 10:45.212
Don't do anything
I wouldn't do.

10:45.212 --> 10:46.747
